# FitCity — Gamified Fitness App with City-Based Competition (v2)

## 🎯 Elevator Pitch
A fitness tracking app where your real-world workouts build a **personal skyline** — a dramatic cyberpunk city visualization of your fitness identity with towering skyscrapers you can explore via helicopter flyover. Compete with friends, build neighborhoods, and prove your crew is the fittest.

---

## 🏗️ Core Concept Breakdown

### 1. One World, Many Neighborhoods (Phased City Model)

Instead of mapping users to real-world cities from day 1 (which creates empty, dead cities), all users start in **one global city: FitCity**. Neighborhoods emerge organically as the user base grows.

| Phase | Trigger | City Model |
|---|---|---|
| **Phase 1: Global Pool** | Launch → 500 users | Everyone in one global FitCity. Single leaderboard, one shared skyline map. Community feels alive even with 50 users. |
| **Phase 2: Neighborhoods Emerge** | 500 → 10K users | High-status users can **found neighborhoods** (geo or interest-based). Users opt-in. Neighborhoods compete against each other. |
| **Phase 3: Geographic Cities** | 10K+ users | Neighborhoods group into real geographic cities. Full inter-city competition unlocked. |

**Why this works:**
- No empty cities — the global pool is always populated
- Neighborhoods only exist when there are enough people to fill them
- Users choose their tribe rather than being assigned to a dead zone
- All user data (skylines, streaks, status) carries over across phases — it's just re-bucketing the social layer

### 2. Task System
- **Examples**: 1hr daily workout (4 days/week), 1hr meditation, 2hr outdoor sports
- Tasks/goals are **pre-curated in v1**, democratic voting in v2
- Users pick which tasks they want to commit to

### 3. Virtual Character & Social Status
- Every user has a virtual avatar/character
- **Social Status** = Σ (Task Difficulty × Streak Multiplier)
- Status unlocks in-game privileges (neighborhood founding, clans, land, influence)

### 4. 🏙️ Fitness Skyline (Signature Feature)

Your fitness data is visualized as a **full 3D cyberpunk city** — real three-dimensional skyscrapers you can walk, fly, and cruise through. Not a flat chart or 2D card — a living, explorable world.

| Building Property | What It Represents |
|---|---|
| **Height** | Streak length — 30-day streak = towering skyscraper |
| **Width** | Activity variety across categories |
| **Color / glow** | Category: cyan=cardio, magenta=strength, green=wellness, amber=sports |
| **Density (buildings per plot)** | Weekly active days |
| **Neon signage** | Task name + streak count glowing on the facade |

**3D World Design**:
- **Full 3D geometry** — modular skyscrapers with Base + Floor stacks + Crown, rendered in Unity URP
- **Cyberpunk palette** — deep purples, pink/magenta sky, cyan/teal neon accent lights, dusk-to-night atmosphere
- **Populated city grid** — each user occupies a 200m × 200m plot; plots placed on a shared world grid separated by roads
- **Lit windows** — emissive window shader: more windows lit = more recent activity
- **Water harbor** — planar reflection at city edge; buildings reflect in water
- **Volumetric atmosphere** — distance fog (purple tint), god rays from sunset, ambient bloom
- **Visibility** — cruise to other users' plots and see their skylines directly in the 3D world
- **Customization** — spend coins to change building skins, materials, effects, and avatar cosmetics

**Building states**:
- 🏗️ Active streak < 7 days: Construction crane on rooftop, scaffolding texture
- ✅ Active streak ≥ 7 days: Complete building, all windows lit proportionally
- 💔 Broken streak: Crack overlay, desaturated materials, flickering lights
- 🔧 Recovered streak: Crack-dissolve heal animation plays
- 🏛️ 365-day streak: Unique landmark tower model (one-of-a-kind architecture)

**Social impact**: Your skyline IS your identity. Cruise past another user's district and instantly read their commitment from how tall their towers stand.

### 4.1 🚁 Cruise & Exploration Mode

Users can **physically cruise through the 3D city** via a third-person avatar — not a fly-over video, but a real explorable 3D world shared with all users in the neighborhood.

**Experience**:
- **Third-person avatar** (hooded character visible behind) moves through the city streets and sky
- **Shared world** — multiple users' plots visible in one continuous city; cruise from your district into your neighbor's
- **Controls** — left joystick to move, right joystick/drag to rotate camera, altitude slider (Street Level ↔ Bird's Eye)
- **Cruise mode** — tap CRUISE to auto-fly forward at set speed (shown in knots), cinematic camera follows
- **Building interaction** — tap any building → holographic glass tooltip: task name, owner, streak length, level, "TAP TO SEE DETAILS"
- **Altitude slider** (right edge) — smoothly transitions: walking (ground level) → flying (mid-air) → bird's eye (top-down)
- **HUD** — altitude in feet, compass direction, speed display, city minimap
- **Capture** — "📸 Capture Skyline" → screenshot saved and shared via native share sheet
- **Searchlight** — helicopter searchlight sweeps across buildings in fly mode

**Multi-user world**:
- Each user's buildings occupy their own named district plot
- Nearby users' districts loaded on-demand as you approach (proximity streaming)
- LOD system: full detail nearby, simplified silhouettes at distance
- District boundary glow ring + floating nameplate ("Alex's District · Level 12")

**Why this matters**: This is a fitness game with a shared persistent world — not just a data visualization. Users are motivated to keep streaks active because their buildings visibly shrink and crack if inactive. Visiting neighbors' cities creates organic social accountability.

### 5. 3-Layer Incentive Model

| Layer | When | What Drives It |
|---|---|---|
| **Personal Progress** | Day 1+ | Character evolution, XP, skill trees, streak badges |
| **Social & Community** | Week 2+ | Leaderboards, neighborhood accountability, rank |
| **Tangible Rewards** | Month 2+ | Partner gym discounts, brand vouchers, sponsored events |

### 6. 🏛️ Neighborhood Creation as a Status Feature

Neighborhood creation is **not an admin task** — it's a **reward** unlocked by high-status users:

- **Requirement**: Reach **Level 10 Status** to unlock the "Found a Neighborhood" ability
- **Founder = Natural Leader**: The founder becomes the neighborhood's first **Mayor** with special powers:
  - Propose neighborhood-wide events and challenges
  - Set motto and customize neighborhood banner
  - Pin announcements for members
- **Naming & Identity**: Founders name their neighborhood, set a description, and choose a theme:
  - Geographic: "Bandra Crew", "Koramangala Squad"
  - Interest-based: "Iron Nation", "Zen Valley", "Cardio Kings"
- **Recruitment Loop**: Founders invite members → more members = taller collective skyline → attracts more members (viral growth)
- **Dual Membership**: Users can join **1 geographic neighborhood** + **1 interest-based neighborhood**, giving dual identity and dual competition
- **Threshold Unlock**: Neighborhood unlocks competitive features (leaderboard, clan wars) once it hits **20+ active members**
- **Mayor Rotation**: Highest-status member becomes Mayor each month — keeps competition alive

**Incentive chain**: Grind for status → found a neighborhood → recruit members → build the tallest collective skyline → become the most powerful neighborhood → attract more members.

### 7. Clans & Land Ownership (Phase 2+)
- High-status users can form clans within neighborhoods and claim virtual territory
- Incentive loop: more tasks → more streak → more status → bigger empire
- **Land** → Build virtual facilities (Gym, Yoga Studio, Sports Arena) that give buffs to clan members
- **Clans** → Participate in Clan Wars (weekly challenges), share resources, group achievements

### 8. Inter-Neighborhood & City Competition
- **Phase 1**: Global leaderboard only (individuals)
- **Phase 2**: Neighborhoods compete on **collective activity volume + consistency** (e.g., "Bandra Crew: 12,000 hrs vs Koramangala Squad: 9,500 hrs")
- **Phase 3**: Geographic cities compete via aggregate neighborhood scores
- Neighborhood-level and city-level aggregate skyline comparisons

### 9. 🫀 Health Impact Engine

Every task shows **projected health gains before the user starts** — turning abstract exercise into concrete, research-backed results. Based on published WHO, AHA, and medical research data (lookup tables, not AI).

#### Impact Metrics

| # | Metric | What It Shows | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **🧬 Body Age** | Composite score — real age minus fitness offset | "You're 30 but your body is 26" |
| 2 | **❤️ Disease Risk Reduction** | % reduction for heart disease, diabetes, stroke, certain cancers, hypertension, osteoporosis | "-12% heart disease risk" |
| 3 | **🧠 Mental Health Score** | Anxiety/depression risk reduction, stress resilience, cognitive sharpness | "+15% stress resilience" |
| 4 | **😴 Sleep Impact** | Sleep quality improvement, deep sleep boost, time-to-sleep reduction | "+12% sleep quality" |
| 5 | **🔋 Energy & Stamina** | Daily energy battery level, predicted boost from today's task | "Energy +20% tomorrow" |
| 6 | **🫁 VO₂ Max** | Cardio fitness level, percentile rank for age/gender, projected improvement | "Better than 72% of 28-year-olds" |
| 7 | **🦴 Bone & Joint Health** | Bone density impact, joint mobility, injury risk reduction | "-40% osteoporosis risk by 60" |
| 8 | **🏋️ Strength Milestones** | Projected strength gains, body composition shift, functional fitness | "Lean mass +0.8kg in 4 weeks" |
| 9 | **⏳ Lifespan Added** | Estimated years added to life expectancy based on activity level | "+0.3 years this month" |
| 10 | **💰 Money Saved** | Projected savings in future medical costs from current fitness level | "₹12,000/year saved" |
| 11 | **🌍 Environmental Impact** | CO₂ saved from cycling/walking instead of driving | "12kg CO₂ saved this month" |
| 12 | **⚡ Recovery Score** | Body recovery %, overtraining risk, optimal next workout | "85% recovered — safe for HIIT" |

#### UX: Health Impact Preview (per task)

When a user taps any task, they see projected gains:
- **Before starting**: "If you complete this: Body Age -1.5yr, Heart Risk -12%, +2,450 kcal burned"
- **After completing**: Celebration screen — "You just reduced diabetes risk by 0.3%!"
- **Weekly report**: Push notification — "This week you added 0.05 years to your life"

#### Skyline Integration
- **Body Age** glows as a golden number above your skyline
- **Lifespan counter** visible on profile — cumulative years added since joining
- **Green trees/parks** appear around buildings for environmental impact tasks

#### MVP vs Later

| Metric | MVP? | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Body Age | ✅ | One number, massive emotional impact, shareable |
| Lifespan Added | ✅ | Unforgettable — no other app shows this |
| Disease Risk (top 3) | ✅ | Concrete, simple lookup table |
| Calories Burned | ✅ | Standard, easy to calculate |
| Money Saved | ✅ | Unique angle, easy math, very shareable |
| Sleep Impact | ❌ v2 | Needs wearable sleep data |
| VO₂ Max | ❌ v2 | Needs running data integration |
| Mental Health Score | ❌ v2 | Sensitive, needs careful design |
| Recovery Score | ❌ v2 | Needs HRV/wearable data |
| Environmental Impact | ❌ v2 | Nice-to-have, not core |

> [!NOTE]
> All health projections include disclaimer: *"Based on population-level research. Not medical advice. Consult your doctor."*

### 10. 🛡️ Streak Protection & Recovery

3 layers of safety — generous for genuine users, unexploitable for gamers:

| Layer | What | Cost | Limits |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Grace Days** | Auto-protects a missed day | Free | 3 per quarter, resets every 90 days |
| **Streak Shield** | Pre-purchased protection | 150 coins | 1 active at a time |
| **Streak Recovery** | Buy back a broken streak | Escalating | Within 48hrs of break only |

**Streak Recovery cost by streak length:**

| Broken Streak | Cost |
|---|---|
| 1-7 days | 50 coins |
| 8-30 days | 150 coins |
| 31-90 days | 300 coins |
| 91-365 days | 500 coins |
| 365+ days | 1000 coins |

**Flow**: Day missed → grace day remaining? → auto-use ✅ → shield active? → auto-use ✅ → neither? → streak broken 💔 → 48hr recovery window → pay coins or lose streak permanently.

**Skyline visuals**: Grace/shield days show subtle shimmer. Broken streak (in 48hr window) shows cracks with a “repair” button. Permanently broken = cracks, height reverts.

